---
// MCP Demo Page
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <title>MCP Demo | AI Tools Lab</title>
    <style>
      body {
        font-family: system-ui, sans-serif;
        max-width: 800px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 20px;
      }
      h1 {
        color: #333;
      }
      .mcp-section {
        margin-bottom: 2rem;
        padding: 1rem;
        border: 1px solid #ddd;
        border-radius: 4px;
      }
      .tools-list {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(200px, 1fr));
        gap: 1rem;
      }
      .tool-card {
        padding: 1rem;
        border: 1px solid #eee;
        border-radius: 4px;
        background-color: #f9f9f9;
      }
      code {
        background-color: #f5f5f5;
        padding: 0.2em 0.4em;
        border-radius: 3px;
        font-family: monospace;
      }
      pre {
        background-color: #f5f5f5;
        padding: 1rem;
        border-radius: 4px;
        overflow-x: auto;
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <h1>Model Context Protocol (MCP) Demo</h1>
    
    <div class="mcp-section">
      <h2>About MCP</h2>
      <p>
        The Model Context Protocol (MCP) is a standard that connects AI systems with external tools and data sources.
        This page demonstrates the integration of MCP with an Astro website.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mcp-section">
      <h2>Available MCP Tools</h2>
      <p>The following tools are available through the astro-mcp integration:</p>
      
      <div class="tools-list">
        <div class="tool-card">
          <h3>get-astro-config</h3>
          <p>Returns the Astro configuration information</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="tool-card">
          <h3>list-astro-routes</h3>
          <p>Lists all the routes in your Astro project</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="tool-card">
          <h3>get-astro-server-address</h3>
          <p>Returns the current server address information</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="tool-card">
          <h3>list-astro-integrations</h3>
          <p>Lists all available Astro integrations</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="tool-card">
          <h3>search-astro-docs</h3>
          <p>Searches the Astro documentation</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mcp-section">
      <h2>How to Connect to MCP Server</h2>
      <p>The MCP server is available at:</p>
      <pre>http://localhost:4321/__mcp/sse</pre>
      
      <p>You can configure most MCP-compatible AI assistants to connect to this endpoint.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="mcp-section">
      <h2>MCP Usage Example</h2>
      <p>Here's a simple example of how to use the MCP tools in an AI conversation:</p>
      <pre>"Please use the list-astro-routes tool to show me all the routes in this project"</pre>
      <p>The AI assistant connected to this MCP server would then be able to use the tool to fetch and display the routes.</p>
    </div>
    
    <a href="/">Back to Home</a>
  </body>
</html>
